I"<p>Here a the most used commands for composer:</p>

<h4 id="start-new-php-project">Start new php project:</h4>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>composer init
</code></pre></div></div>

<h4 id="install-a-new-packages-with">Install a new packages with:</h4>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>composer require packageName
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Use <a href="https://packagist.org/">packagist.org</a> to search for packages</p>

<p>Get the latest version:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>composer update
</code></pre></div></div>

<h4 id="uninstall-packages">Uninstall packages:</h4>

<p>composer remove packageName
Search package from composer:</p>

<p>composer search packageName
Shows a list of installed packages that have updates available:</p>

<p>composer outdated
You should always run the validate command before you commit your composer.json file:</p>

<p>composer validate</p>
